Economy:
   VA Boosts Home Loan Rate
   To 8.5%, Effective Today
Also effective today, the department said it will increase
other maximum rates by half a percentage point. The new
maximum rates will be 8.75% for graduated payment mortgages,
10% for home improvement loans, 11% for manufactured-home
loans, 10.5% for manufactured home lot-only loans, and 10.5%
for manufactured home and lot loans.
   In the fiscal year ended Sept. 30, the department
guaranteed more than 181,000 home loans totaling more than
$15.4 billion. In the first four months of the current fiscal
year, it has guaranteed more than 70,000 loans totaling more
than $6 billion.
   The average loan guaranteed by VA in the current fiscal
year is $86,249.